%% Training Operator (KFTO) - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / API Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Pods as Worker/Master Pods
    participant DNS as Headless Service<br/>(DNS Discovery)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>openshift-monitoring

    Note over User,Prom: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply PyTorchJob/TFJob/...<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-*<br/>443/TCP->9443/TCP, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (Allow/Deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created/Rejected

    Note over Operator,Pods: Reconciliation Loop

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (CR created/updated)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Services<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorchJob)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HPA (elastic PyTorch)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (gang scheduling)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note over Pods,DNS: Flow 2: Distributed Training Communication

    Pods->>DNS: DNS lookup: {job}-{type}-{idx}<br/>plaintext
    DNS-->>Pods: Pod IP resolution
    Pods->>Pods: Inter-pod training communication<br/>Framework-specific/TCP, plaintext
    Note right of Pods: NetworkPolicy restricts traffic<br/>to pods within same job<br/>(PyTorchJob only)

    Note over Prom,Operator: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    Operator-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics
